caption.text:
I think the new Batwoman is forgetting how Batwoman and the Bat Man/Woman Comics themselves came into popularity. Just cause you get hired for a role doesn’t mean you spit in the preexisting faces of the fan base. Which is why this show is gonna flop.——————————————————————
I accidentally disliked this. But this YouTube comment made me laugh regarding the Batwoman show that’s coming out (which is horrible) ... I don’t even get this surge of douchie female actresses, like women need a chip on their shoulder and gotta be assholes to get a foot in. Like l loved all the Underworld Movies, Hunger Games, Twilight, Resident Evil, The original Catwoman movie with Halle Berry? Liked it. So I don’t get it.... we don’t need douchie female protagonist who act like men but say they don’t like white men/men and steal white men’s/men’s ideas... like what? Lol like at some point in the trailer for the show she says “I don’t want a man taking credit for a woman’s work”........ Okay? But you stole everything from Batman while the guy is dead/missing and use it for yourself to not even be a hero but to pick and chose who you wanna save.... The fuck? This show is so bad in so many ways. Real shame..... Like is this fan service? Who asked for this? Heroes teach lessons. This bitch is just a asshole, as a character, They made Batwoman into a total bitch, I swear the original Batwoman was like Bruce’s Granddaughter or a Student, this is just terrible.... I learned something from even Deadpool for fucks sake..... What is Batwoman? For Fucks Sake.... A Asshole? For Fucks Sake, Villain? For Fucks Sake, Anti-Hero? Hey she said, “This Show isn’t for Old White guys” not me.... Damn even I got something out of Captain Marvel. Maybe shitty Superhero Shows are suppose to be pointless.... Who even looks up to these women....? They carry themselves so poorly... Maybe not Brie Larson... But this new Batwoman can kick rocks with her stolen Batsuit...

🇸🇪 DREAMHACK MASTERS MALMÖ 2019 🇸🇪
-----------------------------------------------------------------
El día de mañana comienza el torneo en Suecia.

Esta edición repartirá 250.000 USD en premios y un puesto a IEM Katowice 2020. Contará con 16 equipos divididos en dos grupos. Ambos contarán con upper bracket y lower bracket.

Los partidos comenzarán a las 07:00 A.M hora Argentina y se jugarán siempre dos encuentros en simultáneo durante la primera fase.

Cuatro de los cinco mejores equipos de la actualidad estarán presentes en el torneo. Además habrá presencia brasileña con @furiagg donde veremos el debut de HEN1.

El evento nos ofrecerá, ver los primeros encuentros de shox con @teamvitality, también el primer campeonato de @nipgaming sin @get_rightcs el histórico jugador Sueco, tras su despedida del equipo. Otro momento especial será la vuelta de flusha y Golden a @fnatic sumado al regreso de GuardiaN a @natus_vincere_official .
📷 @dreamhackcsgo

This month last year is what started me thinking down my current path of focusing on Cosplay items for my business.  A friend of mine is always doing something for halloween.  He was struggling to create a Thanos helmet using paper.  2 days before Halloween I asked if he’d like my help.  I went home that night and sculpted this Thanos helmet in VR and started it printing. REVIEW: BORDERLANDS 3

Borderlands 3 chega às mãos do público quase cinco anos após Borderlands: The Pre-Sequel (2014), último lançamento central da franquia com o mesmo estilo de jogabilidade. O game está disponível para Xbox One, PS4, PC (via Epic Games Store) e será lançado futuramente para Google Stadia.

O mais recente shooter looter da 2K Games e Gearbox Software traz um alívio para os fãs do gênero e da série, com conteúdo e diversão de sobra. Apesar disto, o título também incita o questionamento sobre a necessidade de amadurecimento (literal) de uma franquia prestes a completar 10 anos.

Borderlands 3 é um divertido shooter looter, com diversas opções de gameplay dependendo do seu próprio gosto, bem como uma aplausível variedade de localidades a serem exploradas, missões a serem cumpridas e armas a serem usadas. No entanto, o estúpido humor da série permanece intacto, senão retrógrado, e infelizmente descredibiliza o que poderia ter sido uma narrativa minimamente interessante com uma rasa crítica ao comportamento virtual-viciado da sociedade moderna. As tentativas de piadas são, na maioria, imbecis e irritantes. Ignorando os diálogos putrefeitos, a jogabilidade é, em geral, equilibrada e engajante apesar da repetição de fases e de inimigos. Há também muitos bugs pelo caminho, com apenas alguns danificando, de fato, a experiência de jogo.

NOTA: 70/100 - BOM

preview_comments.text: @sparda1981 thanks man! Yeah those steelbooks look really cool, I really want to pick up Sekiro at some point, it looks really good! You have a great day too man!!

@gamer_with_mask I never buy them if they’re in crazy sets when they’re over a £100 but these last couple I’ve got, the Days Gone which came with a nice artbook and my Gears 5 one which is beautiful they were only £10-£15 more than the standard editions so I got them 😄

caption.text:
Swipe to see all images>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>
.
What are some of your favourite Steelbooks, I’ve never really liked them until recently, because I like all my games to be matching, neat and level on the shelf and these things are usually in boxes of all different sizes, but just recently I’ve had a change of heart, some of them look amazing and they have some really cool art on them. This gen I only have 3 steelbooks, I was disappointed ordering the special edition of RDR2 didn’t come with the steelbook, that you had to order the ridiculously overpriced version with everything to receive it, as most standard special editions tend to come in one, for example, the steelbooks from this gen that I own; Days Gone, Batman Arkham Knight and Gears 5, were all just around £15 more expensive than just the bog standard editions and all included beautifully illustrated steelbooks, Days Gone even came with a hardback ‘The Art of’ book, which I love. If you swipe across I’ve also photographed my Resident Evil 5 and 6 steelbooks, which I think look really cool! I do have a few others, included in the first pic is my Beyond Two Souls PS3 Steelbook which I recently picked up in mint condition. I also have Gears 1,2, Clive Barkers Jericho and Crackdown 2. But that is the full extent of my Steelbook collection. I’ll definitely be adding to it in the future though.
.
